extends layout

block content
  .home-hero
    .container
      .home-hero-copy.home-hero-copy-single
        .home-hero-badge Educational Platform
        h1.home-hero-title Blockchain Labs for Modern Cryptography Classes
        p.home-hero-subtitle
          | A clearer, more product-like front door for the demo: students can explore hashing,
          | consensus, mining, fees and signatures as one connected learning system.
        .home-hero-actions
          a.btn.btn-primary.btn-lg(href='/classroom') Open Classroom Mode
          a.btn.btn-default.btn-lg(href='/theory') Review Theory
        .home-hero-meta
          span Built for live teaching
          span Visual + interactive
          span Ready for multiplayer evolution

  .container.home-overview
    .home-section-intro
      p.home-section-eyebrow Product Map
      h2.home-section-heading Choose the concept you want to teach
      p.home-section-lead
        | The homepage is now organized as a guided catalogue: first the teaching direction,
        | then the modules grouped by concept, and finally the classroom-specific layer.

    .home-summary-grid
      .home-summary-card
        p.home-summary-kicker Learning Path
        h3 From hash to consensus
        p Start with core blockchain causality before moving into economic or adversarial scenarios.
      .home-summary-card
        p.home-summary-kicker Classroom Use
        h3 Individual exploration or live demo
        p Each module can work alone, but the structure now makes the overall teaching flow much easier to scan.
      .home-summary-card
        p.home-summary-kicker New Capability
        h3 Multiuser classroom mode
        p Teacher and students can now share the same mempool and chain state in one live room.

    .home-section-stack
      .home-module-band
        .home-band-head
          div
            p.home-section-eyebrow Foundations
            h3 Core Chain Concepts
          p Build intuition from one hash to a distributed ledger.
        .home-cards-grid.home-cards-grid-two
          a.home-card(href='/hash')
            .home-card-kicker Foundations
            h3 Hash Function
            p Explore SHA-256 and the avalanche effect in real time.
          a.home-card(href='/block')
            .home-card-kicker Mining
            h3 Block
            p Tune the nonce and see proof of work emerge from repeated hashing.
          a.home-card(href='/blockchain')
            .home-card-kicker Integrity
            h3 Blockchain
            p Watch a single change cascade through the full chain.
          a.home-card(href='/distributed')
            .home-card-kicker Consensus
            h3 Distributed
            p Compare multiple peers and make ledger disagreement visible.

      .home-module-band
        .home-band-head
          div
            p.home-section-eyebrow Market & Attacks
            h3 Bitcoin Mechanics
          p Push the class toward realistic economic and adversarial scenarios.
        .home-cards-grid.home-cards-grid-two
          a.home-card.home-card-mempool(href='/mempool')
            .home-card-kicker Market Dynamics
            h3 Mempool &amp; Fees
            p Prioritize transactions, collect fees and explain blockspace scarcity.
          a.home-card.home-card-attack(href='/attack51')
            .home-card-kicker Adversarial Thinking
            h3 51% Attack
            p Simulate a double-spend race and discuss why hash power concentration matters.
          a.home-card.home-card-bitcoin(href='/bitcoinblock')
            .home-card-kicker Authentic Data
            h3 Real Bitcoin Block
            p Inspect a real block header and verify its hashing logic live.
          a.home-card.home-card-theory(href='/theory')
            .home-card-kicker Deep Dive
            h3 Block Theory
            p Connect the visuals to the formal structure described in Bitcoin.

      .home-module-band
        .home-band-head
          div
            p.home-section-eyebrow Identity & Verification
            h3 Keys &amp; Signatures
          p Complete the story from ledger state to transaction authenticity.
        .home-cards-grid.home-cards-grid-two
          a.home-card.home-card-key(href='/keys')
            .home-card-kicker Identity
            h3 Key Pairs
            p Generate secp256k1 keys and explain one-way derivation.
          a.home-card.home-card-key(href='/signatures')
            .home-card-kicker Verification
            h3 Signatures
            p Sign any message and show how tampering breaks verification.
          a.home-card.home-card-key(href='/transaction')
            .home-card-kicker Payments
            h3 Transaction
            p Bind sender, recipient and amount into one signed record.
          a.home-card.home-card-key(href='/signedblock')
            .home-card-kicker Integrated Scenario
            h3 Signed Block Lab
            p Sign a transaction, verify it, add it to mempool and mine it into a block.

      .home-module-band.home-module-band-accent
        .home-band-head
          div
            p.home-section-eyebrow Classroom Layer
            h3 Classroom Mode
          p Run the demo as a shared live exercise instead of a single-browser walkthrough.
        .home-classroom-grid
          .home-feature-panel
            .home-feature-panel-head
              h3 What You Can Do
            ul.home-feature-list
              li Create a classroom room and share the code
              li Let students broadcast transactions from their own devices
              li Mine blocks against one shared mempool
              li Reset the scenario or inject background traffic as teacher
          .home-feature-panel.home-feature-panel-muted
            .home-feature-panel-head
              h3 Why It Works in Class
            ul.home-feature-list
              li It makes cryptographic causality visible.
              li Students can break and repair state themselves.
              li Advanced pages already support narrative teaching, not only sandbox play.
              li The codebase is small enough to evolve quickly.
          .home-feature-panel.home-feature-panel-cta
            .home-feature-panel-head
              h3 Start the Shared Lab
            p
              | Launch the multiuser classroom page to create a room and test the live workflow with your students.
            a.btn.btn-block.btn-primary(href='/classroom') Open Classroom Mode

  .container
    p.home-attribution
      | Original demo by 
      a(href='http://andersbrownworth.com/') Anders Brownworth
      |  / 
      a(href='https://github.com/anders94/blockchain-demo/') Source on GitHub
